  "text": "Increasing MATH was significantly related to shorter overall survival among those 74 patients, both as an individual variable and when other prognostic variables were taken into account. [CITATION_1] For plotting survival curves we chose a MATH cutoff of 32, equal to the median of these 74 tumor MATH values. On that basis, patients with high-MATH tumors had twice the hazard of death as those with low-MATH tumors (Fig. 4) . For those who received systemic chemotherapy the high/low-MATH hazard ratio of 4 was even larger (Fig. 5) .",
